						               													<description>In this 18 card Worker Placement game you play as teams of Makers sharing the same small workspace. You will need to share the limited machines while managing your Time and Materials to add completed projects to your Portfolio. Then Submit it to win awards, Prizes and prestige along the way!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You begin the game by making the board out of three Workspace cards and six prize cards,all cards are double sided with unique actions and abilities so each game is different!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players take turns placing their workers into an action space and choosing to take one of the available actions such as; Gaining resources,upgrading resources or attempting to stake a claim on a prize.&amp;#10;Because your Workers are cards, this allows a twist on traditional worker placement. During the game your workers can be flipped; One side blocking your opponents from taking the same action as you, the other allowing your opponent to also take the same action at the cost of returning your worker to you,giving you an extra turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player to submit enough points to one of the available prize cards will get to claim it, gaining victory points and a powerful unique ability they may use for the rest of the game. Abilities such as; gaining an additional worker, being able to take multiple actions with one worker or even choosing where their opponent must place their worker.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player to claim three prizes wins. Or if the 4th/5th prize(depending on player count) is taken and a single player has yet to claim three prizes, then the player with the most victory points will win.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
